Part 5: Add Triad Scale Definitions to FretboardDiagram
File: sarah-practice-plan/src/JungleTools.jsx
The SCALES object in FretboardDiagram currently has pentatonic/modal scales but no triad-specific layouts. We may want to add a way to display just the 3 triad tones across the full neck as a "scale" view. This could be done by either:

Adding triad "scales" (e.g., "am-triad" showing only A, C, E across all strings)
OR relying on chordToneNotes highlighting within existing scales (preferred — simpler, already supported)

Decision: Use chordToneNotes within existing scales rather than creating new pseudo-scales. This keeps the fretboard context (showing the full scale with triad tones ringed) which is more educational.

